comments.body: This is likely related to a database connection issue related to a recent database server migration, I am very sorry for this, and I am looking to further inspect this now.

This is not actually due to any database connection issue, but a file-system issue instead:

```bash
deploy@oawaiver-prod1:~$ ls .ps-su: cannot create temp file for here-document: Read-only file system
```

@kayiwa provided much support in restarting this VM using vSphere, and then using `fsck` in order to repair the corrupted blocks on the file system (thank you very much for this!) I should be in the position to now proceed with redeploying the app. momentarily.

This failure also seems to have corrupted the database entirely:

```bash
oawaiver_prod=# \d
Did not find any relations.
```

@jrgriffiniii I have confirmed with Yuan that the database is functioning normally now. (We have also discovered that I still need admin access to it. I will write a separate ticket.) Thanks so much for your assistance!
Thank you very much for your patience with this, and for alerting me to the error!

dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: Searching queues seem frozen

comments.body:
Trying to clear and repopulate the search queues for the following data sources has *not* led to a resolution of the problem:

- arXiv
- CiNii EN
- CiNii JP
- Crossref
- DBLP
- Europe PubMed Central
- RePEc
- Scopus
- SSRN
- Web of Science (Lite)

It must also be noted that, for the following two Data Sources, there are currently errors blocking the harvesting of metadata:

- Crossref
- PubMed

While trying to retrigger the processing of these enqueued jobs, user search queues are not being actively processed:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/0252f668-e41c-4ed3-a19c-d6276d3c4066)

As I cannot find any information relating to this within the Elements logs, I may need to proceed with requesting support from Symplectic.
This request has been submitted to https://support.symplectic.co.uk/support/tickets/371230. I apologize, as I am not quite certain as to when this might be resolved.
